&lt;p&gt;Oh, this is &lt;em&gt;brilliant&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For every &lt;code&gt;line&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; in the &lt;code&gt;steg64.txt&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; file, of interest are the base64-decoding
of that line.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Originally, I thought that the delta between that and the &lt;em&gt;encoded&lt;&#x2F;em&gt; version of
that decoding was key. However, those extra bits can be derived purely based
on knowing the number of padded bits:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
