&lt;p&gt;See the docs. for
&lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;docs.python.org&#x2F;3.12&#x2F;library&#x2F;dis.html#python-bytecode-instructions&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;dis&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;
for a breakdown of each instruction.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After some attempt to try and determine how to rewrite
&lt;code&gt;open(&quot;&#x2F;flag.txt&quot;).read()#&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; (the trailing &lt;code&gt;#&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; is there to comment-out the
immovable &lt;code&gt;]&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; passed into the &lt;code&gt;eval()&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;) such that it comes &lt;em&gt;out&lt;&#x2F;em&gt; of &lt;code&gt;magic_wand&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;
correctly and failing miserably, the quickest way seems to be to simply
&lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;docs.python.org&#x2F;3.12&#x2F;library&#x2F;dis.html#opcode-JUMP_FORWARD&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;JUMP_FORWARD&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;,
