there are moments of near-silence: each is the &lt;em&gt;inverse&lt;&#x2F;em&gt; of the other.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After mixing them together, the waveform is divided up into second-long chunks,
some where there is an audible sound and the rest near-silence.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
